All right? I could take you
to the top, baby.

13:08.221 --> 13:10.858
-(sighs)
-You know when he see Empire,

13:10.891 --> 13:12.625
he gonna think he died
and went to hip-hop heaven.

13:12.659 --> 13:14.794
-How we supposed to compete
with that?
-You know what?

13:14.828 --> 13:17.297
I am going to need you to be
a little more professional.

13:17.330 --> 13:21.334
Change that outfit.
You look like a box of Skittles.

13:21.368 --> 13:23.036
You don't like this?

13:23.070 --> 13:24.371
I thought you liked these.

13:24.404 --> 13:26.173
Where did we park
the car, Porsha?

13:26.206 --> 13:27.975
Down there.

13:28.008 --> 13:29.642
* Stop, drop

13:29.676 --> 13:32.980
* Shut 'em down, open up shop

13:33.013 --> 13:36.116
-* Oh, no...
-Andre.

13:36.149 --> 13:37.550
What are you doing here?

13:37.584 --> 13:39.319
Damn. Lucious Lyon.

13:39.352 --> 13:42.689
Sonny.

13:42.722 --> 13:44.057
You old head.
How you holding up?

13:44.091 --> 13:45.993
Oh, bobbing and weaving,
like I do.

13:46.026 --> 13:49.029
Well, I think you remember
my eldest.

13:49.062 --> 13:51.498
Andre, I thought that was you.

13:51.531 --> 13:53.800
A grown-ass man.
Heard you just got out.

13:53.833 --> 13:55.735
-Welcome home.
-Thank you, Sonny.

13:55.768 --> 13:58.005
Well, listen, Sonny, you know
why I'm here, right?

13:58.038 --> 14:01.208
Lucious, I got a couple
of contenders,

14:01.241 --> 14:03.376
but I'm still living
month to month.

14:03.410 --> 14:06.046
Sonny, I wouldn't be here

14:06.079 --> 14:08.815
unless it was
absolutely necessary.

14:08.848 --> 14:11.718
For every 20 fighters
I got training here,

14:11.751 --> 14:14.154
there's maybe one
that's special.

14:14.187 --> 14:16.356
You've got a couple of fighters
with some pretty big wins

14:16.389 --> 14:17.524
in the last six months,

14:17.557 --> 14:19.026
and you definitely haven't
invested those funds

14:19.059 --> 14:21.194
in the upkeep,
that's for damn sure.

14:21.228 --> 14:23.063
LUCIOUS:
Well, you know how they say,

14:23.096 --> 14:26.066
it's like the music business,
Andre, sometimes.

14:26.099 --> 14:29.436
The hits pay for
the many painful losses.

14:29.469 --> 14:32.105
Exactly right.

14:32.139 --> 14:34.841
I'll get your money.
I just need a little time.

14:34.874 --> 14:36.709
I know we'll work something out.

14:37.911 --> 14:39.779
Mm-hmm.

14:41.481 --> 14:44.117
* Stop, drop

14:44.151 --> 14:46.686
* Shut 'em down, open up shop.

14:46.719 --> 14:49.122
What the hell were you
doing there?

14:49.156 --> 14:51.724
I figured you'd come here first.
Sonny's got the biggest tab.

14:51.758 --> 14:53.526
Boy, have you lost your mind?

14:53.560 --> 14:55.462
First you disobey me,
and then you're gonna interfere

14:55.495 --> 14:56.796
when I'm trying to collect?

14:56.829 --> 14:59.933
"Boy"? "Disobey you"?
Pop, I'm a man.

14:59.967 --> 15:01.268
That's not how
this works anymore.

15:01.301 --> 15:02.302
-Oh, is that right?
-That's right.

15:02.335 --> 15:04.037
And you let Sonny off easy.

15:04.071 --> 15:06.039
-I was just trying to help you.
-You want to help me?

15:06.073 --> 15:08.541
Learn how to keep
your damn mouth shut.

15:08.575 --> 15:11.078
An-And watch and listen
and learn!

15:11.111 --> 15:12.980
How do you know
he doesn't have it, Pop?

15:13.013 --> 15:14.147
Because I know Sonny.

15:14.181 --> 15:15.949
You walked out of there
empty-handed.

15:15.983 --> 15:17.384
I didn't want you to look weak.

15:17.417 --> 15:19.552
That would have got me
killed on the inside, Pop.

15:19.586 --> 15:21.088
I'm telling you, son,
don't be one of them fools

15:21.121 --> 15:22.489
running around here
wearing your time

15:22.522 --> 15:23.957
like it's some badge of honor!

15:23.991 --> 15:25.458
You were in there
'cause you got caught.

15:25.492 --> 15:28.061
Ain't no honor in that.
I walked in there,

15:28.095 --> 15:30.497
and I talked to Sonny
my damn self.

15:30.530 --> 15:32.599
I didn't send
a bag man or a goon.

15:32.632 --> 15:34.467
That speaks volumes for me.

15:34.501 --> 15:36.403
Or does it mean you couldn't
afford backup, Pop?

15:36.436 --> 15:38.938
Didn't you tell the whole world
the Lyons are flat-ass broke?

15:38.972 --> 15:41.308
I'll tell you what,
if Sonny tells the streets

15:41.341 --> 15:42.976
that Lucious Lyon has gone soft,

15:43.010 --> 15:46.679
Pop, we won't collect a dime.
Not a nickel!

15:46.713 --> 15:49.983
You spent time in there,
served time, did a bid.

15:50.017 --> 15:51.918
Now you gonna tell me
how the streets--

15:51.951 --> 15:54.021
Man, get in the car.

15:57.157 --> 15:58.358
KINGSLEY:
True talent is rare.

15:58.391 --> 16:02.262
But a triple threat--
presence, songwriting chops,

16:02.295 --> 16:04.764
and a voice to match--
it's one in a million.

16:04.797 --> 16:08.435
-And you, Devon,
are one in a million.
-(laughs)

16:08.468 --> 16:10.270
And what we need to do
is take you

16:10.303 --> 16:14.374
from singing background
on Instagram to...

16:14.407 --> 16:16.209
...winning Album of the Year
at the Grammys.

16:16.243 --> 16:19.312
That would be amazing.

16:19.346 --> 16:21.481
* Trust in love

16:21.514 --> 16:25.285
-(cheers and applause)
-* That's what they told me

16:25.318 --> 16:27.020
* Or else you'll be lonely

16:27.054 --> 16:32.159
* I just really want to
touch someone... *

16:32.192 --> 16:34.961
That's my song right there.
How did y'all do that?

16:34.994 --> 16:37.697
-A remix is easy.
-Mm-hmm.

16:37.730 --> 16:41.234
Making you a star, it's a
million times more complicated.

16:41.268 --> 16:44.471
But Empire has something
that nobody else has.

16:44.504 --> 16:47.574
Proprietary analytics.

16:47.607 --> 16:49.409
We know everything
about your audience.

16:49.442 --> 16:51.878
Where they live, what they eat,
what they watch,

16:51.911 --> 16:53.913
and exactly who they're
listening to.

16:53.946 --> 16:56.916
And the data tells us
that a male R&B singer

16:56.949 --> 16:59.219
-needs to have serious swag.
-Mm-hmm.

16:59.252 --> 17:04.091
-Abs, condos, cars, women.
-Mm-hmm.

17:04.124 --> 17:06.726
We'll mold you into
what every man wants to be,

17:06.759 --> 17:08.195
and every woman wants
to sleep with.

17:08.228 --> 17:12.999
So, are you trying to turn me
into a singer or a stripper?

17:13.032 --> 17:14.934
Uh, I just--

17:14.967 --> 17:17.704
I never saw Ne-Yo
have to take off his clothes.

17:17.737 --> 17:20.673
No offense, Mr. Kingsley,

17:20.707 --> 17:23.110
I just-- I don't know
if all of that is me.

17:23.143 --> 17:26.879
-I mean...
-Luther, Marvin, Teddy,

17:26.913 --> 17:28.081
D'Angelo.

17:28.115 --> 17:30.350
The Mount Rushmore of R&B.

17:30.383 --> 17:34.587
And we knew them
by only one name.

17:34.621 --> 17:35.922
And despite the data--

17:35.955 --> 17:39.292
and trust me, it's all legit--

17:39.326 --> 17:42.095
there's still a little magic
left in what we do around here.

17:42.129 --> 17:44.697
See, what you get with Empire

17:44.731 --> 17:47.267
is our ability
to make you a star.

17:47.300 --> 17:51.070
But faster and bigger
than anybody else.

17:51.104 --> 17:55.074
We want to put your face
on the mountain.

17:55.108 --> 17:59.412
Marvin, Luther, Teddy,

17:59.446 --> 18:00.947
(whispering):
D'Angelo...

18:03.450 --> 18:04.784
Devon.

18:04.817 --> 18:08.121
(laughing)

18:08.155 --> 18:09.889
-That sounds good.
-Yeah?

18:09.922 --> 18:11.124
(mouthing)

18:11.158 --> 18:12.825
KINGSLEY:
All right, Becky and Giselle

18:12.859 --> 18:14.827
will show you
to the recording studios.

18:14.861 --> 18:16.563
-Yes.
-We have 11. Take your pick.

18:16.596 --> 18:19.299
-Wow.
-Stop bragging.
He's always bragging.

18:19.332 --> 18:22.101
*

18:23.536 --> 18:25.138
It's like it's you,
but it's not you.

18:25.172 --> 18:27.106
Does that mean you like it
or you don't like it?

18:27.140 --> 18:29.509
It's dope, but it's different.

18:29.542 --> 18:30.943
Yeah, it's for Kai.

18:30.977 --> 18:32.279
It's like me and Tiana.

18:32.312 --> 18:34.814
When we first met,
she changed my sound.

18:34.847 --> 18:35.915
You tell her that?

18:35.948 --> 18:39.352
You know, Mal,
when you love someone,

18:39.386 --> 18:40.920
they always put something on it.

18:40.953 --> 18:43.022
Yeah, they do.

18:47.527 --> 18:49.962
(phone chimes)

19:01.874 --> 19:03.610
Hell no.

19:03.643 --> 19:05.612
(bell tolling)

19:05.645 --> 19:07.547
(horns honking)

19:15.021 --> 19:17.123
So what'd you do,
you drugged me to get on TV?

19:17.156 --> 19:18.991
-(scoffs)
Good morning to you, too.
-Nah, nah, nah.

19:19.025 --> 19:20.327
I'm sorry, I'm sick of
people like you.

19:20.360 --> 19:22.862
You said all of that BS
about paparazzi,

19:22.895 --> 19:24.797
about us not being in New York,
but in actuality,

19:24.831 --> 19:26.466
you're the trash that's
trying to be on tabloids.

19:26.499 --> 19:28.901
What in the hell do you
even get out of that?

19:28.935 --> 19:31.070
Are you done?
Because if you are,

19:31.103 --> 19:32.805
you'd know that I didn't know
we were being followed.

19:32.839 --> 19:34.407
Oh, and if I did,

19:34.441 --> 19:36.008
I would have hidden my face
with my sweatshirt,

19:36.042 --> 19:37.877
'cause getting caught with
a-a messy, drugged-out

19:37.910 --> 19:40.247
American pop star-- that's
poison for a real journalist.

19:42.749 --> 19:44.150
Wait.

19:44.183 --> 19:47.520
Hold up.

19:47.554 --> 19:49.188
What'd you save me for, then?

19:49.222 --> 19:51.358
I don't like seeing people
getting taken advantage of.

19:51.391 --> 19:54.026
It's kind of my job.

19:54.060 --> 19:56.028
Yo, um...

19:58.298 --> 19:59.832
Look, that's my bad.

19:59.866 --> 20:04.203
I... I'm sorry.

20:06.239 --> 20:09.909
I don't usually meet people
that don't want anything.

20:09.942 --> 20:12.445
That's a topic you could spend
all day with your therapist on.

20:12.479 --> 20:14.247
Probably.

20:14.281 --> 20:16.783
(chuckles) Can I go?

20:16.816 --> 20:18.751
Why don't you let me
take you to dinner?

20:18.785 --> 20:21.521
I don't think so.

20:21.554 --> 20:24.791
All right, look,
I promise I'll be...

20:24.824 --> 20:28.428
33% less messy.

20:28.461 --> 20:29.796
-33?
-That's a big deal for me.

20:29.829 --> 20:32.632
How about I'll think
about it? 33%.

20:32.665 --> 20:34.734
(both laugh)

20:41.808 --> 20:43.776
(elevator bell dings)

20:46.279 --> 20:48.448
Jamal? Eric Nelson.

20:48.481 --> 20:51.751
Keem, this is
Kai's assignment editor.

20:51.784 --> 20:53.553
You got good news?

20:53.586 --> 20:57.324
I promised Kai, uh, if we were
ever in this situation...

20:57.357 --> 21:00.226
What situation?

21:00.259 --> 21:03.229
We haven't heard anything
from him in at least 48 hours.

21:03.262 --> 21:05.798
We're using every contact
that we have.

21:05.832 --> 21:07.767
But, in that part of the world,
after this much time,

21:07.800 --> 21:10.770
I have to be honest,
we're worried.

21:22.014 --> 21:23.182
(chuckles)

21:23.215 --> 21:24.784
I get it.

21:24.817 --> 21:26.486
You've been
to the almighty Empire,

21:26.519 --> 21:28.120
so why in the hell
would you sign with folks

21:28.154 --> 21:29.589
working out
of their house, right?

21:29.622 --> 21:33.292
Empire told you
who they'd turn you into.

21:33.326 --> 21:35.695
But did they ask you
who you are?

21:35.728 --> 21:38.498
What do you... what do you mean?

21:38.531 --> 21:41.534
I mean, what motivates you, son?

21:41.568 --> 21:44.270
(sighs) I love my sister.

21:44.303 --> 21:45.538
That's sweet.

21:45.572 --> 21:48.207
-And I love singing in church.
-Right.

21:48.240 --> 21:50.009
No, okay, that's beautiful.

21:50.042 --> 21:51.711
Where does your music
come from, boy?

21:51.744 --> 21:53.012
I don't, I don't know.

21:53.045 --> 21:54.547
-You don't know?
-I don't know. It...

21:54.581 --> 21:55.982
It just comes.

21:56.015 --> 21:57.617
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

21:57.650 --> 22:01.320
Nothing that inspired
just comes.

22:01.354 --> 22:05.392
Now, where does your music
come from?

22:05.425 --> 22:09.562
My heart.

22:09.596 --> 22:10.997
It comes from my soul.

22:11.030 --> 22:14.534
Yes. God has blessed you, Devon.

22:14.567 --> 22:17.537
(chuckles) But all the talent

22:17.570 --> 22:19.406
in the world ain't worth
a hill of beans

22:19.439 --> 22:21.007
if it's used the wrong way.

22:21.040 --> 22:23.876
Why don't you let this family
guide you, and we'll take you

22:23.910 --> 22:25.945
right to the top.

22:29.716 --> 22:32.151
(both laugh)

22:32.184 --> 22:34.587
Can I...

22:34.621 --> 22:38.224
Can I get a minute
to talk to my sister

22:38.257 --> 22:40.326
before I sign?

22:40.359 --> 22:42.429
Sure. Yeah.

22:42.462 --> 22:45.898
-(sighs)
-Don't take too long now.

22:45.932 --> 22:46.966
(chuckles)

22:56.609 --> 22:58.044
This is all you found?

22:58.077 --> 23:00.413
Look, Kingsley's
a Boy Scout, okay?

23:00.447 --> 23:02.949
I could've googled this.
What am I paying you for?

23:02.982 --> 23:04.216
Just wait for it.

23:04.250 --> 23:06.686
See, I've been tailing him,
and turns out

23:06.719 --> 23:08.521
dude loves a field trip.

23:08.555 --> 23:12.091
He's been visiting
a women's prison upstate.

23:14.794 --> 23:15.895
Okay.

23:18.765 --> 23:20.433
(alarm buzzes)

23:25.004 --> 23:26.939
(door locks, keys jangle)

23:38.851 --> 23:40.787
*

