it's got the most

28:06.418 --> 28:08.955
fiery orange sunset
I've ever seen in my life.

28:19.365 --> 28:20.733
It's Dakar.

28:20.767 --> 28:24.070
I mean, not exactly, but...

28:24.103 --> 28:26.538
it's what I love
to do with my music,

28:26.572 --> 28:28.975
make people feel
what I'm feeling.

28:44.290 --> 28:46.692
You want to go to the bedroom?

28:46.725 --> 28:49.628
I've got to go to the office
early tomorrow.

28:49.661 --> 28:53.265
Oh, yeah, yeah, cool, cool.

28:53.299 --> 28:55.367
(chuckles) Yeah, um...

28:55.401 --> 28:57.870
A crazy early morning, too,
so no worries.

28:57.904 --> 28:59.738
-I'll call you.
-Yeah.

28:59.772 --> 29:01.207
But this-this was fun.

29:01.240 --> 29:02.809
We should, we should
do this again sometime.

29:02.842 --> 29:06.112
-JAMAL: Definitely.
-KAI: Okay, cool.

29:09.782 --> 29:11.417
* Yeah

29:11.450 --> 29:12.885
* My life flashes

29:12.919 --> 29:15.054
* Ahead is my desertion

29:15.087 --> 29:18.424
* His trigger finger makes me
contemplate if I deserve it *

29:18.457 --> 29:20.426
* I'd be damned if my family
would take the hit *

29:20.459 --> 29:22.929
* So be a man
and step in front *

29:22.962 --> 29:24.763
* Of this angry man
without a purpose, yeah *

29:24.797 --> 29:26.498
* Tell me this ain't
a conclusion *

29:26.532 --> 29:27.934
* My body can barely react

29:27.967 --> 29:29.836
* I'm thinking
it's just an illusion *

29:29.869 --> 29:31.403
* But the bullet
is telling me facts *

29:31.437 --> 29:33.339
* 'Cause my whole world
is in a spin *

29:33.372 --> 29:35.107
* If they ain't breathing,
I ain't living *

29:35.141 --> 29:36.408
* Can't express this feeling,
praying *

29:36.442 --> 29:38.144
* Give me one more minute,
yeah *

29:38.177 --> 29:40.746
* Lost all control
in the blink of an eye *

29:40.779 --> 29:44.083
* Just a single thought
went across my mind *

29:44.116 --> 29:46.185
* I'm asking, I'm begging,
I'm pleading *

29:46.218 --> 29:47.954
* Just for one more minute

29:47.987 --> 29:49.255
* One more minute

29:49.288 --> 29:52.424
* Eyes open up

29:52.458 --> 29:53.993
* No, it's not my time

29:54.026 --> 29:55.527
* Need to make a choice

29:55.561 --> 29:56.963
-* Am I willing to fight
-Okay.

29:56.996 --> 29:58.630
* I'm asking, I'm begging

29:58.664 --> 30:00.799
* I'm pleading
just for one more minute *

30:00.833 --> 30:02.869
-* One more minute.
-Yo!

30:02.902 --> 30:06.105
Okay, okay. What you been doing?
I see what you been doing now.

30:06.138 --> 30:07.206
I know, right.

30:07.239 --> 30:08.340
-So, look.
-Yo.

30:08.374 --> 30:10.309
This is your best work.

30:10.342 --> 30:12.544
Nah, nah, your hook
is what kills it.

30:12.578 --> 30:13.980
-Yeah.
-Whatever.

30:14.013 --> 30:17.316
It just feels good
to finally get it out, you know?

30:17.349 --> 30:18.517
Yeah.

30:18.550 --> 30:20.519
That's why I hit you up

30:20.552 --> 30:23.389
so that we can
cut the record today.

30:23.422 --> 30:26.692
Okay, but this isn't
for the world to hear.

30:26.725 --> 30:28.694
W-Why not?

30:28.727 --> 30:31.397
-(laughs)
-It's our story. It's real.

30:31.430 --> 30:33.699
Yeah. It's too real.

30:33.732 --> 30:36.135
I'll record it with you,

30:36.168 --> 30:40.072
but only if you promise me
that it's just for us,

30:40.106 --> 30:41.507
nobody but you and me.

30:41.540 --> 30:43.976
-Okay. You ready?
-Yeah.

30:44.010 --> 30:45.577
-All right, let's do it then.
-Yeah. Let's do it.

30:45.611 --> 30:47.413
Start it from the top. (laughs)

30:50.449 --> 30:52.684
(knocking on door)

30:58.690 --> 31:01.027
Uh, hi, I'm Cookie Lyon.
I'm looking for Devon.

31:01.060 --> 31:03.395
-He was supposed to sign
some papers.
-He's not here.

31:03.429 --> 31:05.731
I'm his sister, Janae.
You want to come in?

31:05.764 --> 31:06.933
Okay.

31:06.966 --> 31:09.035
He's told me all about you

31:09.068 --> 31:12.838
and Lucious and Jamal
and Hakeem. (chuckles)

31:12.871 --> 31:14.606
He's so excited.

31:14.640 --> 31:16.442
Yeah, he's really talented.

31:16.475 --> 31:18.377
It's a gift.

31:18.410 --> 31:22.281
Uh, is it just you two?

31:22.314 --> 31:25.284
Yeah, we lost our parents
a few years ago.

31:25.317 --> 31:27.586
I'm so sorry.

31:27.619 --> 31:30.056
Thank you.

31:30.089 --> 31:31.690
Sit.

31:31.723 --> 31:34.693
Okay.
(clears throat)

31:34.726 --> 31:36.862
Ugh, I move real slow,

31:36.895 --> 31:38.330
-but I get there eventually.
-Ah.

31:41.133 --> 31:43.970
I need surgery on this hip,
but Medicare won't cover it,

31:44.003 --> 31:45.471
and since I stopped working,

31:45.504 --> 31:47.273
Devon's working,
like, four jobs.

31:47.306 --> 31:48.874
I hate that he has to do
all that for me.

31:48.907 --> 31:50.109
I'm sure he's not keeping tally.

31:50.142 --> 31:51.577
You'd do the same thing for him.

31:51.610 --> 31:53.712
That's what family does, right?

31:53.745 --> 31:58.450
(chuckles): That sounds
like something my mom would say.

31:58.484 --> 32:01.053
He should be home soon.
You're welcome to wait.

32:01.087 --> 32:04.256
Uh, you know, I have
another meeting I should get to.

32:04.290 --> 32:06.825
But, um, is there something
you would like

32:06.858 --> 32:08.827
-for me to help you with
in here?
-Oh, I'm good.

32:08.860 --> 32:09.861
Um, you want to leave
those papers?

32:11.998 --> 32:14.133
Uh...

32:14.166 --> 32:16.868
no, I'm okay. Thank you.

32:24.710 --> 32:27.013
Becky. Come on in.

32:27.046 --> 32:29.715
-You call me over here to gloat?
-(chuckles)

32:32.851 --> 32:34.987
Um...

32:35.021 --> 32:40.259
Devon is yours, okay?
We're dropping out.

32:40.292 --> 32:41.693
Why?

32:41.727 --> 32:44.763
I can't give him what he needs
right now. Empire can.

32:44.796 --> 32:46.832
And like Lucious says...

32:46.865 --> 32:49.101
-The artist comes first. I know.
-Yes.

32:49.135 --> 32:51.037
-Mm-hmm.
-He said that to me
when he hired me

32:51.070 --> 32:53.005
to be his assistant
and you reminded me of that

32:53.039 --> 32:54.540
the day you promoted me
to head of A&R.

32:54.573 --> 32:58.810
Becky, promise me
you'll get his contract signed.

32:58.844 --> 33:04.116
Okay, get him
that signing money ASAP.

33:04.150 --> 33:07.719
Cookie, I promise you.
I'm gonna take care of him.

33:07.753 --> 33:09.655
Okay.

33:09.688 --> 33:11.990
Okay, we'll pick up
same time tomorrow, okay?

33:12.024 --> 33:14.160
-Yeah. Mm-hmm.
-All right, good night.

33:14.193 --> 33:15.561
Hey.

33:15.594 --> 33:17.996
Where you going?

33:18.030 --> 33:19.498
What are you doing here?

33:19.531 --> 33:21.200
You do remember I used
to work here, right?

33:22.701 --> 33:26.305
Well, it's late, so,
I'm-a just go home.

33:26.338 --> 33:28.006
I've been home already.

33:28.040 --> 33:30.409
I fed the babies,
put them to sleep.

33:30.442 --> 33:32.478
I even gave the nanny
a little extra to stay.

33:32.511 --> 33:34.880
Hakeem, you can't just do that.

33:34.913 --> 33:37.249
Babe, you've been working hard.

33:37.283 --> 33:38.850
I've got something for you.

33:38.884 --> 33:42.054
I-I want to show you
how much I appreciate you.

33:42.088 --> 33:43.555
Come on, let me show you, look.

33:46.225 --> 33:49.195
Just for you, babe.

33:49.228 --> 33:52.698
* Can you focus on me?

33:52.731 --> 33:54.600
I know you like that,
so I made sure

33:54.633 --> 33:59.004
the chef cooked that for you.
Hey, check it out.

33:59.037 --> 34:01.273
Thank you.

34:01.307 --> 34:03.842
Tee, I'm sorry
I'm doing this on the fly,

34:03.875 --> 34:06.945
but I can hold you down.

34:06.978 --> 34:10.849
* Have the faucet's running
and I keep looking at you *

34:10.882 --> 34:16.122
* Stuck on your phone and
you're stuck in your zone *

34:16.155 --> 34:18.090
* You don't have a clue...

34:18.124 --> 34:20.526
Look...

34:20.559 --> 34:25.964
this is, this is really nice,
but we can't, Hakeem.

34:25.997 --> 34:27.933
Everybody went home, babe.

34:27.966 --> 34:32.138
* Lately I've been
a little fed up *

34:32.171 --> 34:37.143
* Wish you would
just focus on me... *

34:37.176 --> 34:40.379
No, nah, nah,
tonight not about me.

34:40.412 --> 34:44.049
It's about you.

34:44.082 --> 34:48.554
* Look me in my eyes

34:48.587 --> 34:51.123
* Ooh.

34:51.157 --> 34:53.292
LUCIOUS:
Hey, how was Devon?

34:53.325 --> 34:55.361
Did he hiccup at the contract?

34:57.529 --> 35:01.533
(sighs)
We said no secrets, right?

35:03.635 --> 35:05.103
Tell me we didn't lose him.

35:05.137 --> 35:08.240
No, I just gave him up
to Empire.

35:08.274 --> 35:10.409
-You what?
-I couldn't look
that boy in the face

35:10.442 --> 35:12.944
and tell him I didn't know
when his money was coming.

35:12.978 --> 35:14.346
His family's broke,
he needs...

35:14.380 --> 35:17.316
Baby, we're broke.

35:17.349 --> 35:19.485
Look, I know your heart's
in the right place, baby,

35:19.518 --> 35:21.920
but all we needed was one month

35:21.953 --> 35:23.855
and we could've got him
a major label deal.

35:23.889 --> 35:25.524
Well, he didn't have
a month, okay?

35:25.557 --> 35:27.759
And I made a decision.
How about that?

35:27.793 --> 35:30.095
-Put some salt and pepper...
-Mr. Lucious.

35:30.128 --> 35:32.531
-Ms. Cookie. You have a guest.
-COOKIE: Devon.

35:32.564 --> 35:34.300
Lucious, this is Devon.

35:34.333 --> 35:37.135
You didn't have to come
all the way out here

35:37.169 --> 35:38.604
to tell me you signed
with Empire.

35:38.637 --> 35:40.272
I know, I understand.

35:40.306 --> 35:43.642
(sighs) No, I came to tell you
that I turned it down.

35:48.046 --> 35:49.114
What are you saying?

35:49.147 --> 35:50.482
Honestly,

35:50.516 --> 35:52.551
Empire showed me
a whole nother world.

35:52.584 --> 35:54.853
And it was everything
that I could imagine,

35:54.886 --> 35:56.955
but you guys made me feel
like I was home.

35:56.988 --> 35:59.491
What about Janae?

35:59.525 --> 36:01.327
She said you made her feel
like family as well.

36:01.360 --> 36:03.295
Well... (chuckles)

36:03.329 --> 36:04.730
Well, come on,
I know you hungry.

36:04.763 --> 36:06.398
Welcome to the family.

36:06.432 --> 36:08.667
Hey, Lucious,
get an extra plate.

36:08.700 --> 36:11.737
-Wow. This kitchen
is pretty crazy.
-(Cookie chuckles)

36:11.770 --> 36:14.706
That was real honorable
what you did, man.

36:14.740 --> 36:17.576
Here, why don't you put that
on them eggs

36:17.609 --> 36:20.078
until you can make
some gold ones with us.

36:22.180 --> 36:25.251
-Family comes first here.
-COOKIE: That's right.

36:25.284 --> 36:27.686
Welcome to ours. We got you.

36:27.719 --> 36:30.422
Thank you, Mr. Lyon. Thank you.

36:30.456 --> 36:32.924
You're so welcome.
Now get some silverware.

36:32.958 --> 36:35.661
-You got to bring your sister
over here sometimes.
-I will.

36:35.694 --> 36:38.096
Welcome home, baby. (chuckles)

36:46.438 --> 36:48.774
(knock on door)

36:52.378 --> 36:54.380
You all right? What's going on?

36:54.413 --> 36:56.315
Um...

36:58.450 --> 37:00.419
This is my reminder of a time

37:00.452 --> 37:03.922
when I-I didn't
look out for myself.

37:03.955 --> 37:06.191
I let somebody lie to me
and this...

37:06.224 --> 37:09.361
well, this tattoo is a reminder
of the power of the truth.

37:09.395 --> 37:13.031
You know it's, like,
6:00 in the morning, right?

37:13.064 --> 37:16.868
When I was diagnosed
three years ago, I...

37:16.902 --> 37:18.304
I thought my world
was gonna end.

37:20.639 --> 37:24.042
I'm HIV-positive,
but I'm undetectable.

37:24.075 --> 37:25.711
If you don't know what
that means, it's...

37:25.744 --> 37:27.479
No, of course I know
what it means.

37:30.115 --> 37:34.620
The virus is really low in your
blood, so it's hard to transmit.

37:34.653 --> 37:37.222
Yeah. I didn't want
to have this conversation

37:37.255 --> 37:39.925
while we were kissing,
so I-I just figured I'd...

37:39.958 --> 37:42.961
6:00 in the morning
is the way to go. (chuckles)

37:42.994 --> 37:46.097
Jamal, I don't want you
to think that I'm not interested

37:46.131 --> 37:49.768
because I am...

37:49.801 --> 37:51.937
very much.

37:51.970 --> 37:54.506
But if-if you don't want to,
if you don't want to do this...

37:54.540 --> 37:57.443
Why wouldn't I want to?
I don't...

37:57.476 --> 38:00.579
Some people got a problem
with it and...

38:00.612 --> 38:02.848
I was afraid you would, too.

38:09.220 --> 38:13.992
I guess I should
let you know that...

38:14.025 --> 38:17.262
I'm negative, so...

38:17.295 --> 38:19.064
I know how to stay that way.

38:21.800 --> 38:23.435
So I don't have
a problem with it.

38:23.469 --> 38:27.506
I think you're perfect.

38:35.381 --> 38:37.616
Mm. Don't get excited.

38:37.649 --> 38:40.452
We're going back to sleep.

38:40.486 --> 38:42.087
Come on.

38:43.989 --> 38:45.190
BECKY:
Hey, hon.

38:50.195 --> 38:53.565
What's going on? You okay?

38:53.599 --> 38:57.335
They can't find him and it's
not some off-the-grid thing.

38:57.369 --> 39:00.539
Okay, so that means to me

39:00.572 --> 39:02.140
that he's still
out there somewhere...

39:02.173 --> 39:04.643
-Please, come on, man, please.
-No, really.

39:04.676 --> 39:06.311
Only reason why he took
this stupid-ass gig

39:06.344 --> 39:07.713
is because I made him come here.

39:10.549 --> 39:13.318
-Where the hell did I put it?
-What are you looking for?

39:13.351 --> 39:15.353
-Just let me help you.
-I put it somewhere smart

39:15.387 --> 39:17.823
'cause he's so damn nosy.
All he did was ever search...

39:17.856 --> 39:19.791
Okay, Jamal,
you need to calm down.

39:25.531 --> 39:27.933
Did you find it?

39:31.570 --> 39:34.573
I was gonna ask him, but...

39:34.606 --> 39:39.110
before he left, but, um...

39:39.144 --> 39:41.813
we got into a fight, so...

39:45.917 --> 39:48.353
Jamal.

39:48.386 --> 39:51.823
It was gonna be
so perfect, though.

40:03.301 --> 40:04.636
I called because
I didn't know what to do.

40:04.670 --> 40:06.572
-He's freaking out and...
-You did the right thing.

40:06.605 --> 40:09.240
-Where are you going?
-Going to look for him.

40:09.274 --> 40:12.110
Oh, no, no, no. So, you
gonna go to a war country

40:12.143 --> 40:13.979
and get yourself lost, too?
I don't think so.

40:14.012 --> 40:15.747
JAMAL:
What are they saying?

40:15.781 --> 40:17.449
(Lucious sighs)

40:17.483 --> 40:19.485
Nobody's seen him
for three days.

40:19.518 --> 40:21.286
Exactly, so I'm going.

40:21.319 --> 40:22.954
You can't go running off
to another continent

40:22.988 --> 40:24.456
without a plan, Jamal.

40:24.490 --> 40:26.658
No, that's all right, Mal.
I'll go with you.

40:26.692 --> 40:28.293
-Wait, wait, no, no.
Everybody stop.
-Okay, now.

40:28.326 --> 40:32.130
Now, look, Mal, I know
how you feel about Kai.

40:32.163 --> 40:33.732
And, I mean, if it was
your mom or your brothers,

40:33.765 --> 40:35.333
I'd be the first one
on the plane...

40:35.366 --> 40:36.968
-Yeah, exactly, so please
just let me go.
-No.

40:37.002 --> 40:39.304
This ain't about to be
a Lyon family production.

40:39.337 --> 40:40.839
No, what we need to do is wait.

40:40.872 --> 40:42.841
I've got a call
into the State Department.

40:42.874 --> 40:44.776
Somebody's gonna give me
some more answers.

40:44.810 --> 40:47.412
I promise. Just be patient.

40:47.445 --> 40:49.114
Patient, okay?

40:53.451 --> 40:55.487
You're not telling me
something, I know that.

40:58.690 --> 41:01.259
Son, um...

41:01.292 --> 41:04.295
they found his wallet
and his cell phone

41:04.329 --> 41:06.732
on the side of a road.

41:09.501 --> 41:12.938
Does that mean that he's dead?

41:12.971 --> 41:15.306
What did they say? Did they say
that that means that he's dead?

41:15.340 --> 41:18.810
That doesn't mean that he's...
No, it doesn't.

41:18.844 --> 41:21.780
-No, baby. It's just,
we don't know yet, baby.
-No.

41:21.813 --> 41:23.448
-So, who does know?
-Wait, wait, wait, wait, just...

41:23.481 --> 41:25.283
Wait, Mom. Hold on, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. Hold on one second.

41:25.316 --> 41:27.819
-We can't just wait, we...
-No, no, no, no, no.

41:27.853 --> 41:31.122
-I need you to calm down.
-No, Mom.

41:31.156 --> 41:33.525
It's okay. There's nothing
we can do right now.

41:33.559 --> 41:35.694
-(crying): I love him so much.
-Okay? I know.

41:35.727 --> 41:38.496
(crying):
I love him so much.

41:38.530 --> 41:40.465
COOKIE:
It's-it's okay.

41:40.498 --> 41:43.001
We gonna get through this,
all right?

41:43.034 --> 41:44.202
(alarm buzzes)

41:51.276 --> 41:55.313
Oh. All of a sudden,
I'm so popular. (chuckles)

41:55.346 --> 41:58.817
Nice to make
your acquaintance, Ms....

41:58.850 --> 42:03.321
Giselle. Sims. Formerly Barker.

42:03.354 --> 42:08.093
Oh, one of Eddie Barker's
many widows. May he rest.

42:08.126 --> 42:10.528
It was all very tragic.

42:12.564 --> 42:14.866
I haven't fully recovered yet.

42:14.900 --> 42:16.267
If we're going
to be friends, dear,

42:16.301 --> 42:19.037
there is one thing that is
paramount and that is honesty.

42:19.070 --> 42:21.873
How broken up about Eddie
could you possibly be

42:21.907 --> 42:24.209
when you've been carrying on
with Jeff Kingsley?

42:24.242 --> 42:27.078
He told you that?

42:27.112 --> 42:30.348
He told me many things.
He's got many secrets.

42:30.381 --> 42:34.352
(scoffs) He blindsided me,
just like the Lyons did to you.

42:34.385 --> 42:37.422
And I need them all to know
that I will never

42:37.455 --> 42:41.727
let that happen again
and I need your help.

42:41.760 --> 42:44.596
The Lyons.

42:44.630 --> 42:48.199
Oh, yes, the Lyons.

42:48.233 --> 42:52.871
Kingsley promised me
he would teach the Lyons.

42:52.904 --> 42:55.774
They need to know how it feels

42:55.807 --> 42:59.244
to put one of your own
into the ground.

43:11.623 --> 43:13.324
(exhaling):
Oh, my God.

43:13.358 --> 43:15.026
What did I do?

44:05.043 --> 44:07.045
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

44:09.047 --> 44:11.182
Now that Empire
has you all fired up,

44:11.216 --> 44:13.518
here are a few more shows
to check out from Fox.

44:16.021 --> 44:17.222
Buckle up, buttercup.

44:19.557 --> 44:21.893
It's real, and it pulls
people together.

44:21.927 --> 44:25.496
-* We're breaking waves
shooting star *
-(siren wailing)

44:25.530 --> 44:29.067
* We live for glory
not forever *

44:29.100 --> 44:30.135
MAN: Touchdown!

44:30.168 --> 44:33.705
* Reach out *

44:33.739 --> 44:37.342
* Make this right here
right now *

44:37.375 --> 44:40.278
* Stand up *

44:41.179 --> 44:42.914
* Here right now *

44:42.948 --> 44:44.716
That sounds like fun.
